1 Creating a literal function
2 Determine the type of a variable 
3 If, else if, else 
4 Switch statement







1 Creating a literal function
function testFun(param1, param2) {
  console.log(param1, param2);
}


2 Determine the type of a variable 
typeof 3
typeof '3'


3 If, else if, else 
if (num > 15) {
  return "Bigger than 15";
} else if (num < 5) {
  return "Smaller than 5";
} else {
  return "Between 5 and 15";
}


4 Switch statement
switch(num) {
  case value1:
    statement1;
    break;
  case value2:
    statement2;
    break;
...
  case valueN:
    statementN;
    break;
}